<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SPICER 14-INCH (355.6 MM) STAMPED ANGLE-SPRING CLUTCH - SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH INSTALLATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
        <title>SINGLE PLATE CLUTCH INSTALLATION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace pilot bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100327">Figure 27</hotlnk>). Bearing must have a press fit.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent damage, install by tapping on O.D. of pilot bearing.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two guide studs 3/8" x 16 thread, 2" long at the top of the flywheel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100328">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the disc by inserting the aligning tool through the spline and into the pilot
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100329">Figure 29</hotlnk>). Make sure the side marked PRESSURE PLATE SIDE faces the
                pressure plate.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100327" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100327" filename="../figg11/G1100327.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 27. Replace Pilot Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100328" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100328" filename="../figg11/G1100328.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 28. Install Guide Studs</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100329" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100329" filename="../figg11/G1100329.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 29. Insert Aligning Tool Through Spline and into Pilot Bearing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the aligning tool still in place, carefully slide the clutch assembly over the aligning
                tool. Align the lock strap or self-adjuster with the access hole in the bell housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100330">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start six 3/8" x 1" Grade 5 or better mounting bolts and lockwashers and hand tighten.
            </para>
            <para>Replace the two guide studs with two mounting bolts. Tighten the mounting bolts to 35 to 40 ft-lbs.
                (47.45 to 54.23 N&#8226;m) according to the sequence shown (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100331">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two wooden blocks from between the release bearing housing and the flywheel ring
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100332">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1100330" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100330" filename="../figg11/G1100330.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Align Lock Strap or Self-Adjuster With Access Hole in Bell Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100331" filename="../figg11/G1100331.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Tighten Mounting Bolts According to Sequence Shown</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100332" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100332" filename="../figg11/G1100332.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Remove Wooden Blocks From Between Release Bearing Housing and Flywheel Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1100333" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1100333" filename="../figg11/G1100333.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Remove Aligning Tool</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the aligning tool (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100333">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
